      "writtenOn": "2020-11-03T13:50:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "To avoid iterating the attributes multiple times, I think we\u0027ll want to combine this with presentation attribute parsing and some form of dynamic dispatch.\n\nAlso, I can\u0027t think of specific examples, but aren\u0027t there cases where intermediate/ancestor classes have (shared) attributes that need to be parsed too?\n\nMaybe we can keep a single iterator control loop in a central place (SkSVGDom/parsing) and have a parseAttribute() virtual on SkSVGNode - then the implementation here would be something along these lines\n\nbool parseAttribute(const char attr_name[], const char attr_value[]) override {\n    // try dispatching to ancestor classes first\n    return INHERITED::parseAttribute(attr_name, attr_value)\n        || SVG_ATTR_PARSE_AND_SET(name, value, \"numOctaves\",...)\n        || SVG_ATTR_PARSE_AND_SET(name, value, \"seed\", ...)\n        || SVG_ATTR_PARSE_AND_SET(name, value, \"type\", ...);\n}\n\nwhere Node::parseAttribute handles all the common presentation attrs.",
      "revId": "eb08fd9592a9ea4a505cd8b8efc2b2bec1b15528",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02"
    },
