        "id": 10818
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-11-03T16:00:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hmm, for the first part -- I think if we use your INHERITED::parseAttribute() concept there\u0027d be no need for a separate iteration to handle presentation attributes, would there? The base SkSVGNode::parseAttribute() would eventually handle fill, stroke, etc, and just set those in its fPresentationAttributes field. This way we could avoid the central iterator control loop, which sort of keeps with the bottom-up idea (attribute parse/set starts at the bottom-most level and bubbles up eventually to SkSVGNode which handles presentation attrs). I might be msising something though.\n\nI\u0027m not totally sure what you mean in the second question (ancestor classes having shared attributes).",
